---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

const article = { author: "Maine Dispensary Guide Editorial Team", publishDate: "2026-01-25", modifiedDate: "2026-03-20", section: "City Guides" };
export const title = "Maine Cannabis Events 2026";
---

<Layout 
  title={title}
  description="Cannabis events and regulatory updates in Maine for 2026. How to stay connected with OCP rule changes and industry events."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1540575467063-178a50c2df87?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop"
  article={article}
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Maine Cannabis Events 2026</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Industry meetups, policy hearings, craft festivals, and networking opportunities across the Pine Tree State</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Policy & Government</h2>
      <Callout title="Stay Connected" type="info">
        Maine's cannabis community is thriving with events year-round. This calendar will be updated monthly as new events are announced. Bookmark this page and check back often!
      </Callout>
      <p>Stay informed about the regulations that shape Maine's cannabis industry. The <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a> holds regular public hearings and stakeholder meetings.</p>
      
      <div class="events-list">
        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>OCP Quarterly Stakeholder Meeting</h3>
          <p class="event-date">March 15, 2026 | Augusta</p>
          <p>Quarterly update from OCP leadership on licensing, compliance, and industry trends. Open to all licensees.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Maine Cannabis Policy Public Comment</h3>
          <p class="event-date">April 2026 | Augusta & Virtual</p>
          <p>Opportunity to provide input on proposed regulatory changes. Check OCP website for agenda.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Legislative Cannabis Caucus Meeting</h3>
          <p class="event-date">May 2026 | State House, Augusta</p>
          <p>Lawmakers discuss upcoming legislation affecting the industry. Open to public observation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>OCP Compliance Workshop</h3>
          <p class="event-date">July 2026 | Portland</p>
          <p>Detailed walkthrough of new compliance requirements for 2026. Mandatory for all licensees.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Annual OCP Industry Summit</h3>
          <p class="event-date">October 2026 | Augusta</p>
          <p>The premier event for Maine cannabis policy. Features regulatory updates, industry speakers, and networking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Industry Meetups & Networking</h2>
      <p>Connect with fellow cannabis professionals at these regular gatherings across Maine.</p>
      
      <div class="events-list">
        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Maine Cannabis Coalition Monthly Meetup</h3>
          <p class="event-date">First Thursday monthly | Portland</p>
          <p>Casual networking for industry professionals. Rotating locations across Greater Portland.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Northern Maine Cannabis Alliance Mixer</h3>
          <p class="event-date">Second Friday monthly | Bangor</p>
          <p>Networking event for Aroostook, Penobscot, and Piscataquis county businesses.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Women in Maine Cannabis</h3>
          <p class="event-date">Third Wednesday monthly | Portland & Virtual</p>
          <p>Support and connect with women-owned cannabis businesses across the state.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Cannabis Tech Maine: Innovation Showcase</h3>
          <p class="event-date">June 2026 | Portland</p>
          <p>Demo day featuring cannabis technology solutions from Maine startups and vendors.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Craft Festivals & Consumer Events</h2>
      <p>These events showcase Maine's cannabis culture to the public and offer brand-building opportunities.</p>
      
      <div class="events-list">
        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Maine Craft Cannabis Festival</h3>
          <p class="event-date">August 14-16, 2026 | Portland Waterfront</p>
          <p>Three-day celebration of Maine's craft cannabis culture. Live music, product sampling, educational sessions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Cannabis & Comedy Night</h3>
          <p class="event-date">April 2026 | Lewiston</p>
          <p>Fundraiser for Maine Cannabis Liberation Project featuring local comedians.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Higher Ground: Maine Cannabis Wellness Fair</h3>
          <p class="event-date">September 2026 | Bangor</p>
          <p>Focus on wellness applications of cannabis. Yoga, nutrition, holistic health.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Maine Grown Showcase</h3>
          <p class="event-date">October 2026 | Augusta</p>
          <p>Annual celebration of Maine's cultivators. Product awards, grow demonstrations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Educational Events</h2>
      <p>Level up your knowledge with these workshops, certifications, and training opportunities.</p>
      
      <div class="events-list">
        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Maine Budtender Certification Program</h3>
          <p class="event-date">Multiple sessions | Portland & Online</p>
          <p>Comprehensive training covering Maine regulations, product knowledge, and customer service. Offered through Maine Cannabis Coalition.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Cannabis Business Fundamentals Workshop</h3>
          <p class="event-date">March 2026 | Augusta</p>
          <p>Two-day intensive for aspiring cannabis entrepreneurs. Covers licensing, finance, operations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Security & Compliance Bootcamp</h3>
          <p class="event-date">May 2026 | Online</p>
          <p>Virtual workshop on Maine security requirements and compliance best practices.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-item">
          <h3>Cannabis Tax & Accounting Summit</h3>
          <p class="event-date">July 2026 | Portland</p>
          <p>Specialized event covering <a href="/glossary/#280e-(internal-revenue-code)">280E</a>, state tax obligations, and financial best practices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Submit Your Event" type="success">
      Know about an event not listed here? Contact the Maine Cannabis Coalition or submit event details through our vendor directory to get it added to this calendar.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Save These Dates</h2>
      <p>Here's a quick reference for the major events throughout 2026:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>March:</strong> OCP Quarterly Meeting, Business Fundamentals Workshop</li>
        <li><strong>April:</strong> Policy Public Comment, Cannabis & Comedy Night</li>
        <li><strong>May:</strong> Legislative Caucus, Security Bootcamp</li>
        <li><strong>June:</strong> Tech Showcase</li>
        <li><strong>July:</strong> OCP Compliance Workshop, Tax Summit</li>
        <li><strong>August:</strong> Maine Craft Cannabis Festival</li>
        <li><strong>September:</strong> Higher Ground Wellness Fair</li>
        <li><strong>October:</strong> OCP Annual Summit, Maine Grown Showcase</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Your Calendar, Your Connection" type="info">
      These events are the heartbeat of Maine's cannabis community. Whether you're new to the industry or a seasoned veteran, showing up matters. Relationships built at these events often become partnerships, mentorships, and friendships that last careers.
    </Callout>

  </article>
</Layout>